{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"928092a5-3f08-4e7c-8a71-2434c86f7548","content":"You already have the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package referenced — that's all the setup needed. Now run your tests in hot-reload (watch) mode:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts a persistent session that watches for file changes. When you save edits to your test or source files, it automatically re-runs the affected tests **without a full rebuild**, giving you a much faster feedback loop.\n\n### Quick workflow\n\n1. **Start it:** `dotnet test --hotreload`\n2. **Edit & save** your `.cs` files in another terminal/editor\n3. **Watch** the test results update automatically in the running session\n4. **Exit** with `Ctrl+C` when done\n\nWould you like me to start it up and begin fixing the failing tests?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ad1c5d05-17b6-4340-8715-79680389d023","outputTokens":185},"id":"dd775131-deba-47ee-b585-9fcbe7eb910a","timestamp":"2026-04-07T15:54:23.943Z","parentId":"74b74b11-20f9-468d-9c27-b0abb6c91e81"}
